<p>Methylene blue might be the most underrated compound in biohacking. It started as a textile dye in 1876, became the first fully synthetic drug used in medicine for treating malaria, and today it's used in hospitals for methemoglobinemia and surgical marking.</p>

<p>It's not technically a peptide. But it shows up in peptide and biohacking circles constantly because it targets something fundamental: how your cells produce energy.</p>

<div class="d">
  <div class="s">What This Guide Covers</div>
